 were recovered\nand analyzed. Preliminary analysis shows that BITSE imaged the solar minimum\ncorona with the equatorial streamers on the east and west limbs. The narrow\nstreamers observed by BITSE are in good agreement with the geometric properties\nobtained by SOHO coronagraphs in the overlapping physical domain. In spite of\nthe small signal-to-noise ratio (about 14) we were able to obtain the\ntemperature and flow speed of the western steamer region in the range 4 to 7 Rs\nas: For the equatorial streamer on the west limb, we obtained a temperature of\n1.0 +/- 0.3 MK and a flow speed of about 260 km/s with a large uncertainty\ninterval.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Nov 2020 22:58:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 12 Dec 2020 12:34:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-20"}
